All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Animal
The Animal class models the animal on the island.
AnimalFactory
The AnimalFactory class creates the specific animal object based on animal species and return it.
AnimalGenerator
The AnimalGenerator class creates the certain number of specific animal objects and return a list of them.
AppleTree
The AppleTree class models the apple tree on the island.
Cat
The Cat class models the cat on the island.
Command
The Command interface define methods needed for staring or pausing island simulation
ConcreteIslandBuilder
The ConcreteIslandBuilder class that assembles the parts of the finished island object
Grass
The Grass class models the grass on the island.
Grub
The Grub class models the grub on the island.
Island
The island class models the island.
IslandBuilder
The islandBuilder interface define methods needed for creating parts for an island
IslandGenerator
The IslandGenerator class creates an island using the islandBuilder interface that is defined
IsntParasite
Class used if the animal isn't parasite
IsParasite
Class used if the animal is parasite
Kiwi
The Kiwi class models the kiwi on the island.
Parasite
The Parasite interface is implemented by animals that are parasites
PineTree
The PineTree class models the pine tree on the island.
Plant
The Plant class models the plant on the island.
PlantFactory
The PlantFactory class creates the specific plant object based on plant species and return it.
PlantGenerator
The PlantGenerator class creates the certain number of specific plant objects and return a list of them.
Rabbit
The Rabbit class models the rabbit tree on the island.
Rat
The Rat class models the rat on the island.
ScrubBrush
The ScrubBrush class models the scrub brush on the island.
Simulation
The Simulation class controls the start or pause of the island simulation
SimulationCommand
The SimulationCommand interface define methods needed for updating parts for island each turn
Sparrow
The Sparrow class models the sparrow on the island.
Water
The Water class models the stream on the island.
Weather
The Weather class models the weather on the island.
